column2: Starbucks is so famous everywhere and I just love to sit and sip coffee and take a bite of their regular pastry. I love the mug which comes with your name engraved but the coca nitrogen is not something different- its same like plain cold coffee, water and ice. Nothing awesome about it.

Oscar a barista at this shop decided a 62 year old writer was not welcome at his shop. I was a fraud, e would bang on the restroom door every time I used it. Used a bogus patron of the week contest to try to provoke me and laughing at me it was so funny. Oscar used friends to start a confrontation. Slanderous lies meant to damage. Sadly this lack of common good behavior is very  normal at all San Francisco coffee shops and Starbucks is no different. Adolescent  behavior or worse. This nation of cowards are about to get what they deserve.
